@startuml "Main Application Architecture with Builder Pattern and Background Processes"
title "Infraware Terminal - Main Application Structure (with Background Process Support)"

' InfrawareTerminal main struct
package "Main Application" {
  class InfrawareTerminal {
    - ui: TerminalUI
    - state: TerminalState
    - classifier: InputClassifier
    - event_handler: EventHandler
    - command_orchestrator: CommandOrchestrator
    - nl_orchestrator: NaturalLanguageOrchestrator
    - tab_completion_handler: TabCompletionHandler
    - history_arc: Arc<RwLock<Vec<String>>>
    - authenticator: Option<Arc<dyn Authenticator>>
    - using_mock_llm: bool
    - cancellation_token_tx: watch::Sender<CancellationToken>
    - job_manager: SharedJobManager
    --
    + builder(): InfrawareTerminalBuilder
    + run(): async Result<()>
    + check_completed_jobs()
    - handle_event(event): async Result<bool>
    - handle_submit(): async Result<bool>
    - handle_command(): async Result<()>
    - handle_natural_language(): async Result<()>
    - handle_tab_completion()
  }

  note right of InfrawareTerminal
    **Microsoft Rust Guidelines Compliance**
    Now implements Debug trait
    (added per compliance requirements)

    **Single Responsibility**
    - Manages event loop
    - Routes events to orchestrators
    - Coordinates UI and state
    - Handles scrolling via TerminalState
    - Monitors background jobs periodically

    **Event Handling**
    - ScrollUp/ScrollDown events
    - Calls state.scroll_up()/scroll_down()
    - TerminalState manages visible_lines
    - OutputBuffer uses visible_lines for bounds

    **Background Process Support (Periodic)**
    - Holds: SharedJobManager field
    - Holds: last_job_check: Instant tracker
    - Periodic check: every 250ms (JOB_CHECK_INTERVAL)
    - Two-phase locking: read first, then write if needed
    - Fail-fast on poisoning: log error, return early
    - Displays completion notifications only on success
    - Non-blocking try_wait() for status checks

    **Job Checking Strategy**
    - Read lock phase: check has_running_jobs()
    - Fast path: return if no jobs exist
    - Write lock phase: call check_completed()
    - Poisoning handling: fail-fast (no recovery)
    - Periodic: reduces lock contention by 25x
      vs per-event checking
  end note
}

' Builder pattern
package "Builder Pattern" {
  class InfrawareTerminalBuilder {
    - ui: Option<TerminalUI>
    - state: Option<TerminalState>
    - classifier: Option<InputClassifier>
    - event_handler: Option<EventHandler>
    - llm_client: Option<Arc<dyn LLMClientTrait>>
    - renderer: Option<ResponseRenderer>
    - command_orchestrator: Option<CommandOrchestrator>
    - tab_completion_handler: Option<TabCompletionHandler>
    --
    + new(): Self
    + with_ui(ui): Self
    + with_state(state): Self
    + with_classifier(classifier): Self
    + with_event_handler(handler): Self
    + with_llm_client(client): Self
    + with_renderer(renderer): Self
    + build(): Result<InfrawareTerminal>
  }

  note right of InfrawareTerminalBuilder
    **Builder Pattern Implementation**
    Provides flexible construction with
    dependency injection support

    **Default Initialization**
    - MockLLMClient for testing
    - Default ResponseRenderer
    - Standard handler chain
  end note
}

InfrawareTerminalBuilder --|> InfrawareTerminal : builds

' Background job management (NEW)
package "Background Process Management (NEW)" {
  class SharedJobManager {
    note as JobMgrNote
      type SharedJobManager =
        Arc<RwLock<JobManager>>

      **Thread-Safe Shared Access**
      - Arc: shared ownership across modules
      - RwLock: reader-writer synchronization
      - Multiple concurrent readers
      - Exclusive writers
    end note
  }

  class JobManager {
    - jobs: HashMap<usize, JobEntry>
    - next_id: usize
    --
    + new(): Self
    + add_job(...): usize
    + list_jobs(): Vec<JobInfo>
    + job_count(): usize
    + check_completed(): Vec<JobInfo>
    + has_running_jobs(): bool
  }

  class JobInfo {
    + id: usize
    + pid: u32
    + command: String
    + status: JobStatus
    + start_time: Instant
  }

  JobManager --> JobInfo : returns cloned

  note bottom of JobManager
    **Non-Blocking Job Tracking**
    - try_wait() for status polling
    - Automatic cleanup on completion
    - 1-based job IDs (bash-style)
    - Safe for event loop integration
  end note
}

' Core dependencies
InfrawareTerminal --> TerminalUI : owns
InfrawareTerminal --> TerminalState : owns
InfrawareTerminal --> InputClassifier : owns
InfrawareTerminal --> EventHandler : owns
InfrawareTerminal --> CommandOrchestrator : owns
InfrawareTerminal --> NaturalLanguageOrchestrator : owns
InfrawareTerminal --> TabCompletionHandler : owns
InfrawareTerminal --> SharedJobManager : owns (NEW)

' Orchestrator integration
CommandOrchestrator --> SharedJobManager : manages background jobs (NEW)

' Event flow
TerminalUI : Ratatui-based rendering
EventHandler : Keyboard input polling
InputClassifier : SCAN algorithm
TerminalState : Buffer management + history
CommandOrchestrator : Command execution workflow + background jobs
NaturalLanguageOrchestrator : LLM query workflow
TabCompletionHandler : Tab completion
SharedJobManager : Background process tracking

@enduml
